** Senior Embedded Software Engineer **

** L3Harris Space and Airborne Systems Australia **

** Eight Mile Plains, Brisbane **

** The Opportunity **

Join a great team of talented professionals with world-class technical
expertise who take a combined approach to software engineering and enjoy
working together.

We are a company on the move and with forecasted growth of L3Harris Space and
Airborne Systems Australia we are now seeking to hire a ** Senior ** **
Embedded Software Engineer ** who will be responsible for architecting and
developing embedded software applications, and participating in the entire
software development life cycle.

Candidates are required to have a good knowledge base of engineering
principles, theories and techniques and a passion for relevant new
technologies. We are mission focused, agile and take innovation seriously.

** Responsibilities **

  * Take responsibility for large and complex areas of the software architecture for multiple software systems. 
  * Develop modular, readable and robust code for defence systems adhering to security and functional requirements in C++ 17. 
  * Participate in all phases of the software development lifecycle, including requirements analysis, systems engineering, agile development, review, testing, integration, and verification. 
  * Presenting design details during customer reviews to a mix of participants with and without software engineering knowledge. 
  * Collaborate effectively with both software and other engineering disciplines as well as management, to ensure comprehensive coverage of requirements as efficiently as possible. 
  * Mentor less experienced software engineers and help them develop good software development and debugging skills. 
  * Write and maintain both internal and deliverable documentation, either directly or through supervision of contractors. 
  * Provide Engineering support to manufacturing as required. 
  * Participate in demo activities for the purpose of sharing knowledge. 
  * Maintain a continuous improvement mindset. 

** Essential Requirements **

  * Degree in Software, Electronics or Electrical Engineering or similar. 
  * Extensive experience in similar role. 
  * Experience architecting complex software for embedded systems, adhering to requirements, with a structured verification approach. 
  * Experience in developing software for microcontrollers in C++ bare metal or with RTOS, working with interfaces such as I2C, SPI, UART, CAN etc. 
  * Ability to work independently or as part of a multi-disciplinary team, adhering to development processes 
  * Excellent computer skills. 
  * Excellent communication skills in English, both verbal and written. 

** Desirable Requirements **

  * An existing NV1 Security clearance. 
  * Ability to read and review schematics, identify issues with hardware designs from a software development viewpoint and make recommendations on HW designs. 
  * Experience developing custom peripheral interfaces on programmable logic. 
  * Experience with complex algorithm design on programmable logic with space constraints. 
  * Experience with python or another scripting language for the purposes of emulation of hardware or software verification 
  * Experience using the Xilinx Zynq SoCs. 
  * Experience in developing firmware in VHDL and/or Verilog for FPGAs. 
  * Experience in developing software to adhere to protocol standards. 
  * Experience in developing mission critical software. 

** **

** About Us **

L3Harris Space and Airborne Systems Australia is a Brisbane based subsidiary
of L3Harris and part of our ICI Division. We provide design, manufacture,
integration and sustainment of advanced electronic warfare components and
subsystems using cutting edge wideband radio frequency and photonic
technology. We are a trusted, sovereign design and production partner to the
Australian Department of Defence and an established exporter to global defence
primes.

L3Harris Technologies is proud to be an Affirmative Action/Equal Opportunity
Employer. We are committed to maintaining a workplace that is free from
unlawful discrimination and offers equal opportunities for all. Applications
from individuals are encouraged regardless of age, disability, sex, gender
reassignment, sexual orientation, pregnancy and maternity, race, religion or
belief, and marriage and civil partnerships.

** A few of our employee benefits are: **

  * 5weeks annual leave 
  * Flexible working hours and hybrid working where possible 
  * Flexible annual leave (buy & sell up to 2 weeks) 
  * Salary continuance insurance (SCI pays 75% of base salary and bonus for up to 2 years) 
  * Discounted private health insurance 
  * Life & Total Permanent Disability Cover 
  * Novated Car Leasing 
  * Salary Sacrifice Extra annual leave 
  * Half day Fridays 

